excluded_counties = ['Southern District', 'Western District', 'Central District', 'Eastern District', 'Northern District', 'Province']
df_excluded = df[~df['Counties and Districts'].isin(excluded_counties)]

# Group the data by county and calculate the total marketed production
grouped = df_excluded.groupby('Counties and Districts').sum()['Marketed Production (\'000 lbs)']

# Sort the data in descending order
grouped = grouped.sort_values(ascending=False)

# Plot the top 10 apple-producing counties in a horizontal bar chart
plt.barh(grouped.index[:10], grouped.values[:10])
plt.title('Top 10 Apple-Producing Counties in Ontario')
plt.xlabel('Total Marketed Production (\'000 lbs)')
plt.ylabel('Counties and Districts')
plt.show()
In [14]:
excluded_counties = ['Southern District', 'Western District', 'Central District', 'Eastern District', 'Northern District', 'Province']
df_excluded = df[~df['Counties and Districts'].isin(excluded_counties)]

# Group the data by county and year, and calculate the total marketed production
grouped = df_excluded.groupby(['Counties and Districts', 'Year']).sum()['Marketed Production (\'000 lbs)']

# Pivot the data to make a stacked bar chart
pivoted = pd.pivot_table(grouped.reset_index(), values='Marketed Production (\'000 lbs)', index='Counties and Districts', columns='Year', fill_value=0)

# Sort the data in descending order by the latest year's production
pivoted = pivoted.sort_values(by=pivoted.columns[-1], ascending=False)

# Plot a stacked bar chart of the top 10 apple-producing counties and districts over the years
pivoted.head(10).plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
plt.title('Top 10 Apple-Producing Counties and Districts in Ontario')
plt.xlabel('County/District')
plt.ylabel('Total Marketed Production (\'000 lbs)')
plt.show()

# Convert the 'Year' column to datetime format
df_excluded['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(df_excluded['Year'], format='%Y')

# Set the 'Year' column as the index
df_excluded.set_index('Year', inplace=True)

# Resample the data to 5-year intervals and calculate the mean price for each interval
mean_prices = df_excluded.resample('5AS')['Average Price (cents/lb)'].mean()

# Print the mean prices for each 5-year interval
print(mean_prices)
